Nominations for CSUSB Alumni Hall of Fame are open till May 7
The three university-wide awards are Distinguished Alumni, Rising Star/Emerging Leader, and Coyote Spirit. The college-linked awards are called the Paw Print Awards. The deadline to submit a nomination is Sunday, May 7, at 11:59 p.m

Read More about Nominations for CSUSB Alumni Hall of Fame are open till May 7









 

 




CSUSB's School of Entrepreneurship is the first of its kind in California
The unique program, which launched in fall 2020, is one of less than 15 existing worldwide. The CSUSB entrepreneurship program is accredited by the Association...


Watch Video about CSUSB's School of Entrepreneurship is the first of its kind in California











 

 




Student to pursue career in biomedical engineering with the goal of becoming a researcher in ulcerative colitis
Jacob Lacy will graduate in May with a bachelor’s in physics and plans on attending the University of Vermont biomedical engineering Ph.D. program to become a...

CSUSB appoints Shareef Amer to lead Coyote Athletics
Shareef Amer, an athletics administrator with more than 11 years of experience in intercollegiate athletics, is CSUSB’s new athletic director.


Read More about CSUSB appoints Shareef Amer to lead Coyote Athletics











 

 




‘Eternal Learning’ points to mission of James R. Watson and Judy Rodriguez Watson College of Education
The mural of ceramic will be formally introduced during a ceremony at 11:30 a.m. Wednesday, May 3, at the college. The work was student-designed, student-created and student-installed.

Read More about ‘Eternal Learning’ points to mission of James R. Watson and Judy Rodriguez Watson College of Education









 

 




Professor of Sociology, Dr. José Muñoz, dedicates his purpose to serve students at CSUSB
Dr. José Muñoz believes that his own lived experiences as a first-generation student help his teaching at CSUSB.


Watch Video about Professor of Sociology, Dr. José Muñoz, dedicates his purpose to serve students at CSUSB

The winners of the Meeting of the Minds Student Research Symposium have been announced
CSUSB recognizes the magnificent graduate and undergraduate researchers and faculty mentors of its 12th annual event.


Read More about The winners of the Meeting of the Minds Student Research Symposium have been announced











 

 




American political activist Angela Davis shares thoughts and experiences with CSUSB community
Angela Davis discussed a variety of topics at the April 17 event, including feminism, intersectionality, social justice, environmentalism and racism.


Read More about American political activist Angela Davis shares thoughts and experiences with CSUSB community











 

 




Sheriff credits CSUSB education in helping to develop his leadership skills
With nearly a 40-year career in law enforcement, San Bernardino County Sheriff and CSUSB alumnus Shannon Dicus credits his college education for not only helping to develop his leadership skills, but also a better, more well-rounded understanding of life.

Read More about Sheriff credits CSUSB education in helping to develop his leadership skills
